## 1. Executive Summary

The **POS Configuration and Session Management Module** is the operational command center of Odoo POS Cafe. It serves as the control layer where authorized users configure POS terminals, manage payment methods, launch and close sessions, and navigate into connected operational screens such as Kitchen Display and Customer Display. This module is not a generic admin panel. It is the intelligent launchpad for running a restaurant digitally.

### Module Objectives

| Objective | Implementation |
|-----------|---------------|
| **Terminal Management** | Create, rename, soft-delete POS terminals with real-time UI updates |
| **Session Control** | Open and close sessions per terminal with financial tracking |
| **Payment Configuration** | Toggle Cash, Digital, and UPI/QR payment methods per terminal |
| **UPI QR Readiness** | Conditional UPI ID field that feeds the QR code generator on checkout |
| **Operational Navigation** | Access Settings, Kitchen Display, and Customer Display from each terminal card |
| **RBAC Enforcement** | Manager has full control; Cashier has view and session access; Kitchen and Customer are blocked |
| **Status Intelligence** | Real-time terminal status badges: Session Active, Ready, New Terminal |
| **Design Continuity** | Maintains the exact same cafe-inspired warm light-mode design from the Auth module |

