### Request Flow --- Terminal Creation

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User Browser
    participant R as React Frontend
    participant A as Axios Interceptor
    participant E as Express Server
    participant P as protect Middleware
    participant AZ as authorize Middleware
    participant V as express-validator
    participant DB as MongoDB Atlas

    U->>R: Click "New Terminal" button
    R->>R: Show CreatePOSTerminalModal
    U->>R: Enter terminal name, click "Create Terminal"
    R->>R: Client-side validation (name length)
    R->>A: POST /api/pos/configs { name }
    A->>A: Attach Bearer token from localStorage
    A->>E: HTTP Request with Authorization header
    E->>P: Verify JWT token
    P->>P: Decode token, find user in DB
    P->>AZ: authorize('manager')
    AZ->>AZ: Check user.role === 'manager'
    AZ->>V: Pass to validation chain
    V->>V: trim, notEmpty, isLength(2-60)
    V->>E: Validation result
    E->>DB: POSConfig.create({ name, createdBy })
    DB-->>E: New document created
    E->>DB: POSConfig.findById().populate('createdBy')
    DB-->>E: Populated config
    E-->>U: 201 { success, config }
    R->>R: Add config to state, select it, close modal
    R->>U: Toast: 'Terminal "name" created!'
```

