## 3. Role-Based Access Control Matrix

### Route-Level Access

| Route | Manager | Cashier | Kitchen | Customer |
|-------|:-------:|:-------:|:-------:|:--------:|
| `GET /pos/config` | Full access | View + session controls | Redirected | Redirected |
| `POST /api/pos/configs` (Create) | Allowed | Blocked (403) | Blocked | Blocked |
| `PUT /api/pos/configs/:id` (Rename) | Allowed | Blocked (403) | Blocked | Blocked |
| `DELETE /api/pos/configs/:id` (Deactivate) | Allowed | Blocked (403) | Blocked | Blocked |
| `PUT /api/pos/configs/:id/payment-methods` | Allowed | Blocked (403) | Blocked | Blocked |
| `POST /api/pos/configs/:id/open-session` | Allowed | Allowed | Blocked | Blocked |
| `POST /api/pos/configs/:id/close-session` | Allowed | Allowed | Blocked | Blocked |
| `GET /api/pos/configs` (List) | All terminals | Active only | Blocked | Blocked |
| `GET /api/pos/configs/:id/sessions` | Allowed | Allowed | Blocked | Blocked |

### UI-Level Feature Visibility

| UI Feature | Manager | Cashier | Kitchen | Customer |
|-----------|:-------:|:-------:|:-------:|:--------:|
| "New Terminal" button | Visible | Hidden | N/A | N/A |
| Terminal cards | Full | View | N/A | N/A |
| Open Session button | Visible | Visible | N/A | N/A |
| Close Session button | Visible | Visible | N/A | N/A |
| Overflow menu - Settings | Visible | Hidden | N/A | N/A |
| Overflow menu - Kitchen Display | Visible | Visible | N/A | N/A |
| Overflow menu - Customer Display | Visible | Visible | N/A | N/A |
| Payment method toggles | Interactive | View-only badge | N/A | N/A |
| UPI ID input field | Editable | Disabled | N/A | N/A |
| "Save Changes" button | Visible when dirty | Hidden | N/A | N/A |
| "View only" lock badge | Hidden | Visible | N/A | N/A |

### Role-Based Query Filtering

```javascript
// server/routes/pos.js --- Line 16
// Manager sees ALL terminals (including deactivated)
// Cashier sees only ACTIVE terminals
const filter = req.user.role === 'manager' ? {} : { isActive: true };
```

### Frontend Route Protection

```jsx
// App.jsx --- ProtectedRoute with allowedRoles
<Route
  path="/pos/config"
  element={
    <ProtectedRoute allowedRoles={['manager', 'cashier']}>
      <POSConfigurationPage />
    </ProtectedRoute>
  }
/>
```

If a Kitchen or Customer user navigates directly to `/pos/config`, the `ProtectedRoute` component blocks access and redirects to `/unauthorized`, which displays a graceful, styled access-denied page with a "Go to My Workspace" button.

