## 4. Database Schema Design

### POSConfig Collection Schema

```javascript
// server/models/POSConfig.js
const posConfigSchema = new mongoose.Schema({
  name:                 { type: String, required: true, trim: true, minlength: 2, maxlength: 60 },
  paymentMethods: {
    cash:               { type: Boolean, default: true },
    digital:            { type: Boolean, default: false },
    qrPayment:          { type: Boolean, default: false },
  },
  upiId:                { type: String, trim: true, default: '' },
  lastSessionOpenedAt:  { type: Date, default: null },
  lastClosingSaleAmount:{ type: Number, default: 0 },
  currentSessionId:     { type: ObjectId, ref: 'Session', default: null },
  isActive:             { type: Boolean, default: true },
  createdBy:            { type: ObjectId, ref: 'User', required: true },
}, { timestamps: true });
```

### POSConfig Field Reference Table

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Validation | Purpose |
|-------|------|:--------:|---------|-----------|---------|
| `name` | String | Yes | --- | 2-60 chars, trimmed | Terminal display name |
| `paymentMethods.cash` | Boolean | No | `true` | --- | Cash payment toggle |
| `paymentMethods.digital` | Boolean | No | `false` | --- | Card/Bank toggle |
| `paymentMethods.qrPayment` | Boolean | No | `false` | --- | UPI QR toggle |
| `upiId` | String | No | `''` | Trimmed | UPI ID for QR generation |
| `lastSessionOpenedAt` | Date | No | `null` | --- | Last session open timestamp |
| `lastClosingSaleAmount` | Number | No | `0` | --- | Revenue from last closed session |
| `currentSessionId` | ObjectId | No | `null` | Ref: Session | Active session reference |
| `isActive` | Boolean | No | `true` | --- | Soft-delete mechanism |
| `createdBy` | ObjectId | Yes | --- | Ref: User | Creator reference for audit trail |
| `createdAt` | Date | Auto | Auto | Mongoose timestamps | Creation timestamp |
| `updatedAt` | Date | Auto | Auto | Mongoose timestamps | Last modification |

### Session Collection Schema

```javascript
// server/models/Session.js
const sessionSchema = new mongoose.Schema({
  posConfig:       { type: ObjectId, ref: 'POSConfig', required: true },
  openedBy:        { type: ObjectId, ref: 'User', required: true },
  openedAt:        { type: Date, default: Date.now },
  closedAt:        { type: Date, default: null },
  status:          { type: String, enum: ['open', 'closed'], default: 'open' },
  totalSales:      { type: Number, default: 0 },
  orderCount:      { type: Number, default: 0 },
  openingBalance:  { type: Number, default: 0 },
  closingBalance:  { type: Number, default: 0 },
}, { timestamps: true });
```

### Session Field Reference Table

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Purpose |
|-------|------|:--------:|---------|---------|
| `posConfig` | ObjectId | Yes | --- | Links to parent POS terminal |
| `openedBy` | ObjectId | Yes | --- | User who opened the session |
| `openedAt` | Date | No | `Date.now` | Session start time |
| `closedAt` | Date | No | `null` | Session end time (null while open) |
| `status` | String | No | `'open'` | Enum: `open` or `closed` |
| `totalSales` | Number | No | `0` | Running total of sales during session |
| `orderCount` | Number | No | `0` | Number of orders processed |
| `openingBalance` | Number | No | `0` | Cash in drawer at session start |
| `closingBalance` | Number | No | `0` | Cash in drawer at session end |

### Database Indexes

| Collection | Index | Fields | Type | Purpose |
|-----------|-------|--------|------|---------|
| posconfigs | `createdBy_1` | `createdBy` | Standard | Filter by creator |
| posconfigs | `isActive_1` | `isActive` | Standard | Active terminal queries |
| sessions | `posConfig_1_status_1` | `posConfig, status` | Compound | Fast active session lookup |
| sessions | `openedBy_1` | `openedBy` | Standard | User session history |

### Entity Relationship Diagram

```mermaid
erDiagram
    USER ||--o{ POSCONFIG : creates
    USER ||--o{ SESSION : opens
    POSCONFIG ||--o{ SESSION : has
    POSCONFIG ||--o| SESSION : currentSession

    USER {
        ObjectId _id
        String fullName
        String email
        String role
    }

    POSCONFIG {
        ObjectId _id
        String name
        Object paymentMethods
        String upiId
        Date lastSessionOpenedAt
        Number lastClosingSaleAmount
        ObjectId currentSessionId
        Boolean isActive
        ObjectId createdBy
    }

    SESSION {
        ObjectId _id
        ObjectId posConfig
        ObjectId openedBy
        Date openedAt
        Date closedAt
        String status
        Number totalSales
        Number orderCount
        Number openingBalance
        Number closingBalance
    }
```

