## 6. Session Lifecycle Workflows

### Session Open Flow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["User clicks 'Open Session' on terminal card"] --> B["POST /api/pos/configs/:id/open-session"]
    B --> C{"Terminal exists?"}
    C -->|"No"| D["404: Terminal not found"]
    C -->|"Yes"| E{"currentSessionId set?"}
    E -->|"No"| F["Create new Session document"]
    E -->|"Yes"| G{"Existing session status?"}
    G -->|"'open'"| H["400: Session already open"]
    G -->|"'closed' or missing"| F
    F --> I["Session.create({ posConfig, openedBy, openingBalance })"]
    I --> J["Update POSConfig:"]
    J --> J1["currentSessionId = session._id"]
    J --> J2["lastSessionOpenedAt = session.openedAt"]
    J1 --> K["config.save()"]
    J2 --> K
    K --> L["Populate session.openedBy"]
    L --> M["201: Return session"]
    M --> N["Frontend: Toast 'Session opened! Ready for orders.'"]
    N --> O["Frontend: fetchConfigs(true) to refresh terminal cards"]
    O --> P["Terminal card status: 'Session Active' with pulsing green dot"]

    style A fill:#FFF7ED,stroke:#F97316
    style P fill:#ECFCCB,stroke:#65A30D
    style D fill:#FEF2F2,stroke:#EF4444
    style H fill:#FEF2F2,stroke:#EF4444
```

### Session Close Flow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["User clicks 'Close Session' on terminal card"] --> B["POST /api/pos/configs/:id/close-session"]
    B --> C{"Terminal exists and has currentSessionId?"}
    C -->|"No"| D["400: No active session to close"]
    C -->|"Yes"| E["Fetch Session by currentSessionId"]
    E --> F{"session.status === 'open'?"}
    F -->|"No"| G["400: No open session found"]
    F -->|"Yes"| H["Update Session:"]
    H --> H1["status = 'closed'"]
    H --> H2["closedAt = new Date()"]
    H --> H3["closingBalance = body.closingBalance or totalSales"]
    H1 --> I["session.save()"]
    H2 --> I
    H3 --> I
    I --> J["Update POSConfig:"]
    J --> J1["lastClosingSaleAmount = session.totalSales"]
    J --> J2["currentSessionId = null"]
    J1 --> K["config.save()"]
    J2 --> K
    K --> L["200: Return closed session"]
    L --> M["Frontend: Toast 'Session closed successfully.'"]
    M --> N["Terminal card reverts to 'Ready' status with amber badge"]

    style A fill:#FFF7ED,stroke:#F97316
    style N fill:#FEF3C7,stroke:#F59E0B
    style D fill:#FEF2F2,stroke:#EF4444
```

### Complete Session Lifecycle State Diagram

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> NewTerminal: Terminal created
    NewTerminal --> SessionOpen: User clicks "Open Session"
    SessionOpen --> SessionActive: Session document created
    SessionActive --> SessionClosing: User clicks "Close Session"
    SessionClosing --> Ready: Session closed, config updated
    Ready --> SessionOpen: User opens new session

    state NewTerminal {
        Badge: "New Terminal" (Blue)
        LastSession: "Never"
        LastClosing: "INR 0"
    }

    state SessionActive {
        Badge: "Session Active" (Green, pulsing)
        Button: "Close Session" (Red)
        OrdersFlow: Orders can be processed
    }

    state Ready {
        Badge: "Ready" (Amber)
        LastSession: Date of last session
        LastClosing: Revenue from last session
        Button: "Open Session" (Orange)
    }
```

