## 8. Critical Functions and Implementation

### 8.1 fetchConfigs --- Terminal Data Loader

```javascript
// POSConfigurationPage.jsx --- Lines 24-40
const fetchConfigs = useCallback(async (showRefresh = false) => {
  if (showRefresh) setRefreshing(true);
  try {
    const res = await posAPI.getConfigs();
    if (res.data.success) {
      setConfigs(res.data.configs);
      // Auto-select the first terminal if none is selected
      if (res.data.configs.length > 0 && !selectedConfig) {
        setSelectedConfig(res.data.configs[0]);
      }
    }
  } catch (err) {
    toast.error('Failed to load terminals');
  } finally {
    setLoading(false);
    setRefreshing(false);
  }
}, [selectedConfig]);
```

**Key Behaviors:**
- Wrapped in `useCallback` with `selectedConfig` dependency to prevent infinite re-renders
- Auto-selects the first terminal on initial load so the payment sidebar is never empty
- Supports two modes: initial load (`showRefresh=false`) and manual refresh (`showRefresh=true`) with spinner

### 8.2 handleTerminalCreated --- Optimistic UI Update

```javascript
// POSConfigurationPage.jsx --- Lines 46-51
const handleTerminalCreated = (newConfig) => {
  setConfigs((prev) => [newConfig, ...prev]);   // Prepend to list
  setSelectedConfig(newConfig);                  // Auto-select the new one
  setShowCreateModal(false);                     // Close modal
  toast.success(`Terminal "${newConfig.name}" created!`, { icon: '...' });
};
```

The new terminal appears instantly at the top of the grid. No page reload. No refetch. The populated config from the server response is used directly.

### 8.3 handlePaymentUpdate --- Selective State Merge

```javascript
// POSConfigurationPage.jsx --- Lines 75-88
const handlePaymentUpdate = async (configId, paymentData) => {
  try {
    const res = await posAPI.updatePaymentMethods(configId, paymentData);
    if (res.data.success) {
      // Update only the changed config in the array
      setConfigs((prev) =>
        prev.map((c) => (c._id === configId ? res.data.config : c))
      );
      setSelectedConfig(res.data.config);
      toast.success('Payment methods updated', { icon: '...' });
    }
  } catch (err) {
    toast.error('Failed to update payment methods');
  }
};
```

Uses functional state update (`prev.map(...)`) to surgically replace only the affected config, keeping other cards untouched.

### 8.4 Terminal Status Derivation

```javascript
// POSTerminalCard.jsx --- Lines 19-20
const hasActiveSession = config.currentSessionId && config.currentSessionId.status === 'open';
const sessionStatus = hasActiveSession ? 'active' : config.lastSessionOpenedAt ? 'ready' : 'new';
```

This derives a three-state status from two data fields, creating an intelligent state machine for the terminal badge.

### 8.5 Payment Method Dirty-State Detection

```javascript
// PaymentMethodConfigPanel.jsx --- Lines 21-24
const handleToggle = (setter, field) => (val) => {
  setter(val);       // Update the toggle state
  setDirty(true);    // Mark the form as modified
};
```

The "Save Changes" button only appears when `dirty === true`, preventing unnecessary API calls and providing clear user feedback about unsaved changes.

### 8.6 Payment Config Sync on Selection Change

```javascript
// PaymentMethodConfigPanel.jsx --- Lines 13-19
useEffect(() => {
  setCash(config.paymentMethods?.cash ?? true);
  setDigital(config.paymentMethods?.digital ?? false);
  setQrPayment(config.paymentMethods?.qrPayment ?? false);
  setUpiId(config.upiId || '');
  setDirty(false);    // Reset dirty state on terminal switch
}, [config._id, config.paymentMethods, config.upiId]);
```

When the user clicks a different terminal card, this effect syncs the payment panel to show that terminal's payment settings. The dependency array includes `config._id` to ensure it triggers on terminal selection changes.

### 8.7 Session Open API Handler (Backend)

```javascript
// server/routes/pos.js --- Lines 177-218
router.post('/configs/:id/open-session', authorize('manager', 'cashier'), async (req, res) => {
  const config = await POSConfig.findById(req.params.id);

  // Guard 1: Terminal existence
  if (!config) return res.status(404).json({ message: 'Terminal not found' });

  // Guard 2: Prevent double session
  if (config.currentSessionId) {
    const existingSession = await Session.findById(config.currentSessionId);
    if (existingSession && existingSession.status === 'open') {
      return res.status(400).json({ message: 'A session is already open' });
    }
  }

  // Create session + link to config atomically
  const session = await Session.create({
    posConfig: config._id,
    openedBy: req.user._id,
    openingBalance: req.body.openingBalance || 0,
  });

  config.currentSessionId = session._id;
  config.lastSessionOpenedAt = session.openedAt;
  await config.save();
});
```

### 8.8 Payment Method Update Handler (Backend)

```javascript
// server/routes/pos.js --- Lines 141-173
router.put('/configs/:id/payment-methods', authorize('manager'), async (req, res) => {
  const { cash, digital, qrPayment, upiId } = req.body;
  const update = {};

  // Type-safe boolean checks (prevents truthy/falsy bugs)
  if (typeof cash === 'boolean') update['paymentMethods.cash'] = cash;
  if (typeof digital === 'boolean') update['paymentMethods.digital'] = digital;
  if (typeof qrPayment === 'boolean') update['paymentMethods.qrPayment'] = qrPayment;
  if (typeof upiId === 'string') update.upiId = upiId.trim();

  // Data integrity: clear UPI ID when QR is disabled
  if (qrPayment === false) update.upiId = '';

  const config = await POSConfig.findByIdAndUpdate(
    req.params.id, update, { new: true, runValidators: true }
  ).populate('createdBy', 'fullName username');
});
```

**Key Design Decisions:**
- Uses `typeof` checks instead of truthy/falsy to handle `false` values correctly
- Uses MongoDB dot notation (`paymentMethods.cash`) for partial subdocument updates
- Auto-clears UPI ID when QR payment is disabled for data consistency
- Returns populated document for immediate frontend use

